Long-term Everton target David Henen looks set to join Olympiacos from Anderlecht in a £3million deal.

Despite Henen spending weeks with Everton, training under the watchful eye of manager Roberto Martinez at their Finch Farm headquarters, Sportsmail understands the highly-rated 18-year old is on his way to Greece.

Henen had also repeatedly expressed his wish to join Everton on social media

